{"command":"cd /data/zrwang/auto-opt/utils/llvm-141753 && cat <<'CODEEOF' | python $AGENT_TOOLS_DIR/apply_code.py write llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp 2019 2019
  // The general form is:
  // (icmp eq/ne (and (add A, Addend), Msk), 0)
  // where A is in some range, and the combination checks if A is inside a strided set of elements.
  // Actually, wait, `add A, C` and `and C_mask`.
  // If `icmp eq (and (add A, Addend), Msk), 0`, we are testing if the bits set in Msk are all zero in `A + Addend`.
  // Equivalently, `A + Addend & Msk == 0`.
  // If `Msk` is `~((1 << K) - 1)`, i.e. it masks out the lower K bits.
  // Then `(A + Addend) & ~((1 << K) - 1) == 0` means `0 <= A + Addend < (1 << K)`.
  // Wait, in our example:
